SIMPLE: rattoon
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rattoon
<hw>Rat*toon"</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧t*t⟦oomac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>reto⟦ntil⟧o</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of the stems or shoots
of sugar cane of the second year's growth from the root, or later. See
<er>Plant-cane</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rattoon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rattoon
<hw>Rat*toon"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Rattooned</conjf> <pr>(-t⟦oomac⟧nd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Rattooning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>reto⟦ntil⟧ar</ets>.]</ety> <def>To sprout or spring up from the
root, as sugar cane from the root of the previous year's
planting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raucid</ent>⟦br⟧
